{"id":19374,"date":"2025-05-20T17:26:13","date_gmt":"2025-05-20T15:26:13","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/?p=19374"},"modified":"2025-05-20T17:27:49","modified_gmt":"2025-05-20T15:27:49","slug":"palestinian-ambassador-pays-courtesy-call-on-deputy-speaker","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/palestinian-ambassador-pays-courtesy-call-on-deputy-speaker\/","title":{"rendered":"Palestinian Ambassador pays courtesy call on Deputy Speaker"},"content":{"rendered":"<p><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"size-medium wp-image-19375 alignleft\" src=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/D-SPEaker-300x113.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"113\" srcset=\"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/D-SPEaker-300x113.jpg 300w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/D-SPEaker-1024x384.jpg 1024w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/D-SPEaker-768x288.jpg 768w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/D-SPEaker-1536x576.jpg 1536w, https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-content\/uploads\/2025\/05\/D-SPEaker.jpg 1600w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px\" \/><\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoListParagraph\"><strong>\u00a0Eino Vatileni<\/strong><\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Non-Resident Ambassador of the State of Palestine to Namibia, H.E. Hanan Jarrar paid a courtesy call to the National Assembly today.\u00a0\u00a0She was welcomed by the Deputy Speaker Hon.Phillipus Katamelo.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">The aim of the visit was to strengthen diplomatic engagements with the State of Palestine.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">In her address, Ambassador Jarrar provided an update on the dire situation in Gaza, highlighting the devastating impact of the ongoing conflict.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">\u201cWhat is currently happening in Palestine is total destruction. Refugee camps are being destroyed, homes demolished, and innocent civilians are being forced to flee their homeland,\u201d she said.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">During the meeting, Ambassador Jarrar expressed her appreciation for Namibia\u2019s unwavering solidarity and continued support for the Palestinian cause, both at the national level and across various international forums.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">\u201cWe are grateful for Namibia\u2019s unwavering support at different platforms including when Namibia took Israel to the International Court of Justice (ICJ) in The Hague, and at many other occasions even during the president\u2019s State of Nation Address. We are grateful that there are people supporting us,\u201d she said.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">She said that she looks forward to future engagements with Namibia for collaborations and parliament to parliament cooperation, including the establishment of a Friendship Group with the Palestine Parliament in the future.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">Deputy Speaker Katamelo reaffirmed Namibia\u2019s principled stance in support of the Palestinian people, emphasizing the country&#8217;s historical commitment to justice, peace, and self-determination.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">He reiterated that Namibia remains an advocate for a peaceful resolution to the conflict and will continue to voice its support on regional and global platforms.<\/p>\n<p class=\"x_MsoNormal\">\u201cNamibia cannot be relentless if others are not safe. Our history of war relates to what Palestine is currently going through and we commit to support Palestine. Namibia believes in solidarity, we are because of solidarity,\u201d Hon. Katamelo said<\/p>\n","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>\u00a0Eino Vatileni Non-Resident Ambassador of the State of Palestine to Namibia, H.E. Hanan Jarrar paid a courtesy call to the National Assembly today.\u00a0\u00a0She was welcomed by the Deputy Speaker Hon.Phillipus Katamelo. The aim of the visit was to strengthen diplomatic engagements with the State of Palestine. In her address, Ambassador Jarrar provided an update on&hellip;<\/p>\n","protected":false},"author":16,"featured_media":19375,"comment_status":"closed","ping_status":"closed","sticky":false,"template":"","format":"standard","meta":[],"categories":[159,39],"tags":[],"class_list":["post-19374","post","type-post","status-publish","format-standard","has-post-thumbnail","hentry","category-home-page-slider","category-news","category-159","category-39","description-off"],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/19374","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/16"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=19374"}],"version-history":[{"count":1,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/19374\/revisions"}],"predecessor-version":[{"id":19376,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/19374\/revisions\/19376"}],"wp:featuredmedia":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media\/19375"}],"wp:attachment":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/media?parent=19374"}],"wp:term":[{"taxonomy":"category","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/categories?post=19374"},{"taxonomy":"post_tag","embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.parliament.na\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/tags?post=19374"}],"curies":[{"name":"wp","href":"https:\/\/api.w.org\/{rel}","templated":true}]}}